13/11/2007
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- A Defence and Security Council, responsible for decisions regarding the army's command, was established in Podgorica on Monday (November 12th). 
The council consists of President Filip Vujanovic, Parliament Speaker Ranko Krivokapic and Prime Minister Zeljko Sturanovic. 
The council will assess the security situation in Montenegro and decide on any measures required. 
(Vijesti - 13/11/07; RTCG, Focus - 12/11/07)
